snippet.title: Amber Heard opens up about being domestic abuse survivor
snippet.description:
New Delhi, Nov 28 (ANI): Actor Amber Heard talked about being a domestic abuse survivor. E! Online reported that in an interview with an American magazine, Glamour she asked about the aforementioned topic without remarking ex-spouse Johnny Depp’s name. She said that, “A woman is always met with “skepticism, hostility and shame” whenever she decides to talk about the injustice she faced. A man, on the other hand, never faces such a stigma. In 2017, ‘Pirates of the Caribbean’ actor denied domestic abuse allegations leveled contrary to him.  It’s over two years since the couple filed for divorce.
